　　Annika Marks is an American actress, writer and producer. Marks started off her career in 2001 in the short-film G Spots?. In 2002 she had a guest starring role on Law & Order: Criminal Intent as Leeza Goldman. In 2003 she had a small role in Mona Lisa Smile. In 2004, Marks starred in the independent drama, The Undeserved. She is perhaps best known for her role in the 2012 drama The Sessions alongside Helen Hunt, William H. Macy, and John Hawkes. The film received wide critical acclaim. In 2014, Marks had the lead role in the indie film Grace..
